node.text:
New Moon in Virgo ❊ September 6 / 7
New Moons happen at the start of a new lunar cycle, they are a reset, a fresh start, a time to honour the things we have gone through and then set new intentions and goals. 

This beautiful earthy New Moon is all about stepping into your power, raising your vibration and remembering just how worthy you are. 

It’s time to come back home to yourself. 
Over these next few days hold focus on how you can step more into your power. What do you have to offer this world? How do you want to shine your light?

Journal prompt for this New Moon:
What habits and routines of mine can I change to live more in alignment with who I want to be?

If you would like more info on this New Moon you can download my September energetics guide through the ebooks section of my website, which includes a heap of journal prompts, oracle spread, manifesting ritual, plus more!

node.text:
Balsamic Moon in Leo 𖡼 
This is the last lunar phase, also known as a waning crescent and happens just before the birth of the New Moon.

This phase is the final release before a new cycle, a time of deep reflection and gratitude. Turn your attention within and shine light on any emotional blockages that have been holding you back from manifesting your dreams. Name each emotion, each feeling and where you feel this pain in the body. Honour what you have been through, hold space for those feelings and then let go.

Intuition intensifies during this time and insights come through strong, which can leave us feeling exhausted. Resting your body and your mind is extremely important during a balsamic moon. Be courageous and speak up about things that truly matter to you, put your trust in the universe and know that everything is unfolding exactly how it is meant to.

Journal prompt for this time:
What is my heart calling me to do? 

Beautiful art is by @earthartlab

node.text:
Later today Mercury our planet of the mind will shift into the diplomatic, beauty loving Libra. 

Mercury determines the way we think, how we articulate information and how we communicate with ourselves and others. 

As Mercury enters into the balanced sign of Libra we feel a harmonious shift, that brings us lessons on how we can look at all perspectives and be a little more mindful of one another’s circumstances. 

Libra is ruled by Venus, the planet of love and the divine feminine, with this energy coming together with our goddess energy of our sun in Virgo, this is a time to really embody your femininity ~ be soft, flow with the wind, have deep intimate conversations, spend your time with the amazing women around you, love and be love.

Channelling these anxieties and emotions into a creative outlet can help you to feel grounded and clarity. This 1S the time to be kind to yourself, let yourself relax, refresh, rest and put trust in your intuition. sistersvillage'.

node.text:
Mercury in Virgo opposite Neptune in Pisces and is currently at its peak today at 22°

This alignment also heightens messages from spirit and messages in dreams. Try and journal down your dreams as soon as you wake up and then come back to these over the next few weeks to decipher. 

Neptune is still currently in retrograde which influence has been shining light onto things that have been going on in the shadows and breaking down those perfect illusions around us. This retrograde has been and still is working to wake us up to what’s really been happening around us. 

Today’s journal prompt:
What do I need to feel safe in this exact moment? Can I give this to myself?

The Moon is currently in the dreamy sign of Pisces, this shift heightens your emotions, sensitives and illusions. This time is all about connecting with your spirituality and the you within even deeper - the soul beyond the physical body.

Ride the wave, go with your own divine flow, be present, meditate, star gaze and take a long bath. This is the time for deep reflection over the insights that came through for you over the weekends Full Moon in Aquarius, be still with all that you are feeling at the moment. 

Journal prompt for today:
What has been coming up for me these past few days?

node.text:
Full Moon in Aquarius 𖡼 August 22
This is our second Full Moon in Aquarius for the year, which very rarely happens making this full moon extra special and super magical. 

This Full Moon in Aquarius illuminates the things, situations and people that we just need to be free from. It’s time to move forward, it’s time for you to purge and release, for you to expand. 

This is a time to revisit the themes that have been coming up for you over the past month. Have you been listening to those whispers within or have you been distracting yourself from what needs to happen? 

Falling on the last day of Leo season at 29° this represents an end of a cycle, a chapter of your life coming to a close. Self awareness is heightened, really feel into the insights that are flowing through right now. 

Journal prompt for Full Moon in Aquarius:
What type of person do I want to be?
Write down everything from the personality traits you want to embody, the goals you want to have achieved, the habits you want to have, your routine, how you feel, who you are surrounded by, as many details as possible. 

If you would like more info on this Full Moon, including a Full Moon ritual and mantra, an oracle spread plus more info on the Full Moon and the planetary influences for the month of August you can download my monthly energetics guide through the website.
